VIOLIN.JS README

ABOUT

    A D3.js 4.0 implementation of violin plots. violin.js exports a function,
    violin(), that can be used to build the plot and specify options in the
    same function chaining manner used by D3.

REQUIREMENTS

    D3.js 4.X

DATA FORMAT

    violin.js requires an array of objects for input. Each object represents a
    separate violin that will be drawn in the plot. Some object fields are
    required. The objects must be in the following format:

        {
            category
                [string; required]
                category and X-axis label for this violin

            id
                [string; required] 
                unique ID for this violin

            values
                [array; reqired]
                an array of numbers used for drawing the violin distribution

            color
                [string; optional]
                hexadecimal code (#012345) used to color the violin

            lowerBound
                [float; optional]
                lower bound value used to cut off the violin drawing

            upperBound
                [float; optional]
                upper bound value used to cut off the violin drawing
        }

OPTIONS

    The following options can be used to alter the behavior and appeance of the
    violin plot.

    data
        [array; required]
        The array of objects used as input for the plot. This is the only
        exported option that is required.

    height
        [int; default = 800]
        The height of the SVG in pixels.

    width
        [int; default = 900]
        The width of the SVG in pixels.

    font
        [string; default = 'sans-serif']
        The font family to use when drawing text.

    fontSize
        [string; default = '11px']
        The font size to use when drawing text.

    fontWeight
        [string; default = 'normal']
        The font weight to use when drawing text.

    kernelBandwidth
        [float; default = 50]
        The kernel density estimation bandwidth parameter. Depending on the
        distribution of the input data, this value will most likely have to be
        increased or decreased.

    xDomain
        [array]
        Specify a custom x-axis domain. The default set of x domain values is 
        the list of categories specified by each violin object. This probably
        shouldn't be used

    yDomain
        [array]
        Specify a custom y-axis domain. The default y domain used is the min
        and max of all values used when estimating the distribution.

    xLabel
        [string; default = '']
        A string used to label the x-axis.

    yLabel
        [string; default = '']
        A string used to label the y-axis.

EXAMPLES

    Create a simple violin plot.

        var plot = violin()
            .data(someData)
            .height(350)
            .width(600)
            .draw();

